

Big query offers access to structured **data storage**, **analytics** which is cost effective and widely used by multiple business. You can easily connect your BigQuery account to the **BCC (Brand Control Center)**. Firstly follow the below steps to build the BigQuery connection with the Google Cloud account.

  
**Step 1**: Open your google cloud account, create a service account and click on **Edit** permission.
  

![](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXfmAcCmt2AuNSzB5OPNWrYD6ND21pei3vQ4BhIlZ-4rGHfQWjaQVV-blzoa7B2fnzoN_Xr4x4-nzEaIFqzVDe5V4HZ-DBvGm4UJKaE7AnQxB7j2jRlTgWvR-pNZRC6y803k9NmYdg?key=NJAxIqXiZeNiZiAibwOlOvRw)

  
**Step 2**: Assign the role.

-   **2.1**: Role = BigQuery Data Editor
     

![](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXdLa2_9j3k3vVWK--V1BASsqdHsdBnaSFOWo7vN2H-Asje-xBbkZQzCSnQUCGqxJJCn3kZLEW9RpKzndTX1tL8GLeUpjhh4SD4auM7zp34n_p4E-QJdno0rKDJ56V3EVBATGS8G6w?key=NJAxIqXiZeNiZiAibwOlOvRw)

  
**Step 3**: Set the condition as shown in the image.

-   **3.1**: Set **Condition 1** as **Service** > **is** > **bigquery.googleapis.com**
    
-   **3.2**: Set **Condition 2** as **Name** > **Starts with** > **projects/<project_name>/<data_set_name>**
    

![](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXfov9Xi08W3cToXh43Cdzpm6B8rtQp1vAZNJfRPwyWPmqlOTZjMLTwbnAub1FLEO4Jfol556OFPzfTmYbS5FFlRuXoPvD-_J7ezLaHoID1sXBQ1mJAjm5p56_aH90lvwkLousvV6g?key=NJAxIqXiZeNiZiAibwOlOvRw)
  
  

Following are the steps to connect your **BigQuery** account with BCC (Brand Control Center).

  

**Step 1**: Login to BCC

**Step 2**: Navigate to **Settings** > **Data Sources** > **Big Query**

  

![](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXdlgo2J8sCdf-8hsdBIqxknHeSMbF4oXr8Sw9shnyUINlaToqRUyxd6taysKJtRMMXnrFVRSP2nYuKQoLywr7kjc14fIJWDb1HNJjT1UVmRdbf-ThuOONuVVz9vOKwSTpb41WyM9g?key=NJAxIqXiZeNiZiAibwOlOvRw)

  

**Step 3**: **Select Account type** (**User** or **Service**),

  

-   **For User**  

Insert the **Dataset ID** (`project_name.dataset_name`) and set the **frequency** (**Daily**, **Weekly**, **Monthly**) to send the Data. **Sign in with Google** to connect the BigQuery account.

  

![](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXd967EQJHP_PhQxXHTdOTmszyjvF5MPlCkhOkC7mPpf6QI578qS96J1PKoTb3bzbVrDoJaU-4pk1Qy2nRNlk6_e6u34-vUJ96QHzwMxGK-CWYVEPZ3IvkQDjscibLM59CdO9b1x?key=NJAxIqXiZeNiZiAibwOlOvRw)

  

-   **For Service**
    

![](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXdXMTYGaOXl0Foc-PbS6TeV5cNPymFWjWAVJ01FuphqkpgcqvybOXAiY57381a4i_BWXQU7wCOVQ6Au3KQPejtJ85cnQpex7DUHCuIh5RzipfzfDy_vEw68ZZojl-EwWlc3_tm61g?key=NJAxIqXiZeNiZiAibwOlOvRw)

  

**Note:** If you have selected the **Service** as an **Account Type** then you have to upload the [JSON authentication file](https://support.google.com/a/answer/7378726?hl=en#:~:text=the%20service%20account-,Click%20APIs%20&%20Services,Click%20Close) along with dataset name

  

After uploading all the details click on the **Connect** button to connect the **BigQuery** account.

![](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXfeAP_SMGr1wu6FrUf-3woCz-dKHr2qTUcj3QK3mt0fkpuqHoHtpPV_q42jf81b4D1pUvYd9Qx3Q-penItJLeDmvv0XXiAwmd79KSphu9HEoROXPrBMj5zRy1atboGQ3lLm8fda?key=NJAxIqXiZeNiZiAibwOlOvRw)

  

![](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXdh6j1UroLFa_NLLc7M-3UDX3y7wy5HxPDNQTaFcKu39BAkA2Yf5bXlRstRmi7XpOGmMYRWbykY2zCHIROHdOnUclRvxx_Xj23SO9NAJ-UwOQdyj5Jn9rb2mqofhhpzeR5mH1HRpA?key=NJAxIqXiZeNiZiAibwOlOvRw)

  

**Connection**

Once the connection is successfully built then a table named “**genuin_data**” will be created under your dataset.  

![](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXfQcq4UFgidCogvvXFV8lJCwxgGTwV3AD7V4ExDz8eacdcfV6ANKsDRCsERCcQe2D-w-NlhD2rqfbRa3KfnCOFvhdffWgIPTOAkSwYZneU_U7ss_FuIzDQik7gQqh-3fU7S29_gDw?key=NJAxIqXiZeNiZiAibwOlOvRw)


All of the data will be passed based on the below structure.

![](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXfuKH4e75YxulPX6lbmB7cCue4JeF-Oueyl48blQh81i0rxKEuCSh8XHbCFM8DycO5l2Vv6OiCH51cmrLf1qgCBJB-FPCBCcFFolVFVMPmP27DYZe4vA5ee-gpXGLAeiyXNdgGdMQ?key=NJAxIqXiZeNiZiAibwOlOvRw)

  
**Disconnection**  

Once the **BigQuery** account is connected then you can also **Disconnect** it.


![](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXfz2eAd3tq6YXCcpWBwBwIuEDUa96UlKkRw0qNlj4TytjcackHaXQkKjEcjvGrIMnKGtqxZHWRqpKHPhLelDpGWadNMMYJRyC-dwdrqD7lWpC5_7eDAwsh-oo8TT63poWkYkznf1Q?key=NJAxIqXiZeNiZiAibwOlOvRw)
 

Confirm the **Disconnection** request as shown in the below screenshot.  
  

![](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXfobkVmWO5EcFu6VEI-o922a32Zxh8PbnK3rEfjgMQmURRgtzaYKwV8AAe-0tUkd27IolKcgpVvHGpl-04zadFN10bPEyk8XFNjpXfRkdk3ew6dAPO3bFv_sK5VT9werM4DRwhYsA?key=NJAxIqXiZeNiZiAibwOlOvRw)


Once the connection is successfully disconnected then a toast message will be visible.

![](https://lh7-rt.googleusercontent.com/docsz/AD_4nXdzqVWbSBHejzhazz2iOiDisJkfrq6Ey5fIfsaEpxCyIsPWmob2Nz76lgq2IQlqVAisIPrCnqQngoI4NwhJtEp_HmzpRbP24j2zcZH67Dj-0uXFrHu5QewBmSN73eC6CqaNLT1m?key=NJAxIqXiZeNiZiAibwOlOvRw)

  

Now the data will not be sent further although the past data will remain the same.
